The Red Devils secured third place in the Premier League on the final day of the season with a 2-0 (0:0) win over direct rivals Leicester City.
The Foxes now have to settle for the Europa League, because FC Chelsea still passed and also qualified for the King's Cup as fourth.
In the fight against relegation, Aston Villa were able to cheer.
Manchester United took the lead with a penalty kick from Bruno Fernandes (71st minute).
After a red card for Leicester City in extra time, Jesse Lingard (90.+8) reached the final.
Chelsea, in the Champions League eighth-finals opponent of FC Bayern, won thanks to Mason Mount (45. + 1) and Olivier Giroud (45. + 4) in parallel with 2:0 (2:0) against the Wolverhampton Wanderers.
"It means a lot to me", said coach Frank Lampard, who is in his first season as Chelsea coach and is in the FA Cup final against Arsenal.
Chelsea's victory over Wolverhampton also benefited Tottenham Hotspur, who with a lean 1:1 (1:0) at Crystal Palace still passed the Wolves and started sixth in the Europa League.
