There was a point missing at the end.
Liverpool, who have been English champions since the end of June, secured a club record with a 3-1 (1:1) win over Newcastle United.
99 points is the highest the Reds have ever scored in a football season.
Coach Jürgen Klopp and his team narrowly missed the points record in English football.
The best score is held by Manchester City with 100 points in the 2017/18 season.
After Newcastle's lead in the first minute, Virgil van Dijk (38), Divock Origi (59) and Sadio Mané (89) took the lead for Liverpool on Sunday.
